RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 57. Claiming Purse 18500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 7 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $1 5,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NIGHT LIVIN dueled briefly, bid at the half-mile pole, drew clear and held sway under mild urging. GLORIOUS JUSTICE stalked the pace in the four path, bid at the three-eighths, then couldn't get to the winner. DULCE VICTORIA raced in the four path but had no late bid. FAIR FOLLY saved ground to no avail. RED ROSEBUSH raced evenly. CORIMA dueled early inside before giving way. PER RULING EAD2023-37 FROM THE INDIANA RACING COMMISSION, NIGHT LIVIN WAS DQ'D DUE TO A POSITIVE TEST.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 2 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ST. ELMO pressed the pace early while in the three path, cleared in mid-turn, was put under pressure outside the eighth pole then repelled that challenge and cleared late. TRICOLOUR bobbled at the start, raced in the two path into the far turn, bid two wide and in the three path through the turn, continued in the three of four path into the lane, was a serious threat with an eighth to go then had to settle for second best. GLEN AIRY settled off the early pace while in the two path, bid three wide and in the four path through the turn when moving closer, came into the lane from the four or five path and flattened out. FUJIN bid four wide and in the five path through the turn, swung into the lane from the six path and tired. GUNNER BAY pressed the pace along the inside into the far turn and was done along the rail. The race was hand-timed due to a timer malfunction.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 25000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $16,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 7 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VARTON was clear early and drew off in the stretch under mild urging. MIA BABY chased the winner and proved second best. KEEN ICE SIGHT gained the show spot late. FOREVER HOME saved ground before fading in the drive. AWESOME LAWSON turned her head at the start and was away tardily. After an inquiry she was declared a starter.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 4 1 1/16M Turf CR: 89. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 1/16 on the main track. (Rail at 36 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMOKEY MANDATE pressed the dawdling pace two wide through mid-turn, was asked in late turn and into the lane, was well clear when straightening then drew off under a strong hand ride. CABLE BOSS was along the inside through the turns, never far back into the far turn, came off the rail and into the two path for the drive, could not gain on the winner then was under a drive to save the place spot. GETTLEMAN raced along the inside into the far turn, steadied while running up on slower rival in mid-turn, continued near the rail into the lane and moved up for the minor share. AIR MARSHAL set the pace along the inside through late turn while under pressure then gave way entering the lane. THE MOTTO raced off the rail into the far turn, bid four wide through the turn when getting closer, swung into the lane from the six path then flattened out late. HIGHEST RATED (IRE) chased the pace from the three path into the far turn, bid three wide and between rivals through late turn, came into the lane from the five path and tired. SCHOOLMASTER (GER) never a factor while near the rail through the turns. CLOSE TALKER chased the pace while along the inside through mid-turn then was empty turning into the lane.

ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, off rail, bid 4wd turn, 6path1/8, flattened late

Non-winners Of A Race Since June 7 Allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Ente red For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZZY JOJO was off awkwardly, vied early between foes, bid entering the turn, drew off, was under strong handling through the stretch and geared down late. LILMISS SASSYPANTS was bumped at the start, chased the winner but was no match for that one. FOREVER BLESSED improved position late. D' KITTEN stalked the pace in the four path, then faded in the stretch. TRYINFORJUSTICE vied early inside before giving way.

ENTRY.COMMENT: awk start,vied early btw,bid7/16,strong handling str,geared down

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 6 5F Turf CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 28000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 5 furlongs on the main track. (Rail at 36 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DESIGNATED hopped at the start and trailed briefly, raced in the two path through the turn, angled into the five or six path for the drive and methodically edged up from mid-track to be up in time. BAYTOWN BAMA GIRL raced along the inside through the turn, shifted into the four path for the drive and was closing with the winner to be up for the place spot. GREEN GRACE chased the pace from the two or three path into the turn, continued between rivals through the lane when near the front then weakened late. LADLE bid three wide through the turn, moved to near even terms with an eighth to go then faltered late. PRETTY VEGAS set the pace on a clear lead into the turn, was joined by two rivals in mid-turn, continued to duel with those through the lane then gave way late. TIDBIT was in the three path through the turn when near the back, came into the lane from the eight path and never was a factor. MASTER THE TACTICS dropped far back into the far turn, continued to lose ground into the lane and was eased to the wire and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOBALS set the pace while under pressure through the turn, shook clear outside the eighth pole opened his largest advantage with an eighth to run and was kept to the task to the end while not seriously threatened. CHARCOAL was in mid-pack while in the three path through the turn, was asked for more in late turn, came into the lane from the six path, continued with good energy inside the eighth pole and gained the place spot late from mid-track. JUST MIGHT chased the pace from the two path through the turn, tipped into the three path into the lane, had aim on the winner while moving closest to that one inside the eighth pole, slowly gained late but lost the place spot at the wire. SHIMMER ME TIMBERS pressed the winner two wide through the turn, lost contact into the lane then weakened late. UNPREDICTABLE BAY was in the three path through the turn, came into the lane from the five path and finished evenly from mid-track. MAJOR WAGER was put in tight early while between rivals, steadied out to last, trailed into the lane then was never in it. DON'T WAIT UP never a factor while along the inside. DIAMOND CITY was put in tight with the rail early and jostled, raced near the inside and never made an impact.
